First of all, the wait time is very long. They have messed up my orders so many times (which means even longer wait times). If I didn't have a dietary restriction, I would just take whatever they gave me just to avoid the headache. They'd also charged me different prices for the same order. By going back multiple times, I was rooting for this local black owned business but my experience has consistently been very disappointing. That's why I stopped going. The food is delicious but not worth the headaches.

The 2 stars was for the quantity of food. I'm going to post pictures you be the judge. I'm going to give it another try, however I'm going to pick up my order. Uber could be the blame the food was cold. Yes cold not warm. So I'll give them that one. But!!! Packaging was awful. Spend some money on packaging. Get Sommer Brown bags to staple close. My food was in a single plastic bag with a knot. The food it self was in a card board paper like tray. No staples, no tape, no aluminum, no stretch tie. This leaves an open door for food tampering. I'm not for it. There was no shrimp in the shrimp and crab meal. You really could not tell irr was crab it was so much sauce.  My cat fish was burnt, my chicken sliders were hard and dry on a bun with syrup. No lettuce, no pickles. Again I'll give it another try but I'll pick my food yoo next time.
